examples.en: The rock shattered the window.
The wine glass shattered
The explosion shattered the building.
A loud scream shattered the silence.
I wasn't just disappointed, I was absolutely shattered.
Their hopes and dreams were shattered by war.
His dreams were shattered by their rejection.
By the time we got home we were both shattered.
The end of his marriage shattered him emotionally.
The news of her husband's death shattered her life.
The plate shattered when it hit the floor.
A scream shattered the late afternoon calm.
He dropped the vase and it shattered into pieces.
His lies and deception shattered my trust in him.
The plate hit the floor, and shattered into tiny bits.
The glass from the shattered windshield cut into her forehead.
It would have shattered in flinders long before it did that damage.
A few weeks in a tiny damp room soon shattered his illusions about university life.
The Marshall Plan sought to regenerate the shattered Europe of 1947.
Your peace will be shattered when the tourist season gets underway (=starts).
Their boat was shattered into matchwood against the rocks and sank instantly.
